parties.raw_snippet:
THIS AGREEMENT ("Agreement"), entered into on May 20, 1992, is between
Arkansas Western Pipeline Company ("Transporter"), an Arkansas corporation, and
Associated Natural Gas Company, a division of Arkansas Western Gas Company,
("Shipper");
parties.reasoning: The opening recitals identify the contracting entities. They explicitly name Arkansas Western Pipeline Company as "Transporter" and Associated Natural Gas Company (a division of Arkansas Western Gas Company) as "Shipper." These are the main parties to the agreement.

contract_type.raw_snippet:
TRANSPORTATION SERVICE AGREEMENT
UNDER RATE SCHEDULE FTS OR ITS
contract_type.reasoning: The document's title and the substantive provisions (e.g., Article II describing Transporter's obligations to transport and redeliver natural gas and Shipper's obligations to tender gas) show the primary purpose is the transportation of natural gas service. Therefore it is a Transportation Agreement.

notice_period.raw_snippet:
Thereafter, this Agreement shall be effective month to month, until terminated
by Transporter or Shipper upon the following written notice to
the other specifying a termination date: sixty (60) days for
interruptible transportation under Rate Schedule ITS and 180
days for firm transportation under Rate Schedule FTS.
notice_period.reasoning: This clause sets the advance written notice required to terminate the month-to-month continuation after the primary term; it is the notice required to stop the continuing (renewed) month-to-month arrangement. It specifies 60 days for interruptible service and 180 days for firm service.

expiration_date.raw_snippet:
Subject to the General Terms and Conditions of Transporter's
FERC Gas Tariff and Rate Schedule FTS/ITS, this Agreement
shall be effective as of the date of physical completion of
and initial deliveries on Transporter's pipeline and shall
continue for a primary term of ten years. Thereafter, this

Agreement shall be effective month to month, until terminated
by Transporter or Shipper upon the following written notice to
the other specifying a termination date: sixty (60) days for
interruptible transportation under Rate Schedule ITS and 180
days for firm transportation under Rate Schedule FTS.
expiration_date.reasoning: Article V.1 defines the term: effectiveness begins on the date of physical completion and initial deliveries and continues for a primary term of ten years, then continues month-to-month thereafter. This is a relative term (primary term of ten years then month-to-month).
expiration_date.normalized_value: primary term of ten years; thereafter month-to-month

renewal_term.raw_snippet:
Thereafter, this

Agreement shall be effective month to month, until terminated
by Transporter or Shipper upon the following written notice to
the other specifying a termination date: sixty (60) days for
interruptible transportation under Rate Schedule ITS and 180
days for firm transportation under Rate Schedule FTS.
renewal_term.reasoning: The clause states that after the initial ten-year primary term the agreement continues on a month-to-month basis (i.e., it renews/continues automatically each month until proper notice is given). That is a month-to-month renewal term.
renewal_term.normalized_value: month-to-month renewal (automatic continuation after ten-year primary term)
